⚙️ The 3 Modes (starter set)

1. 🌊 Float Mode (your “high-like” state)

Goal: light, detached, slightly euphoric

Protocol:
	•	Breath: slow (4–4–8)
	•	Eyes: half-closed or closed
	•	Focus: behind the eyes / forehead
	•	Phrase (repeat mentally):
“Looser… lighter… drifting…”

Add-on:
	•	Slightly sway your body or head (very subtle)

Expected effect:
	•	Time softens
	•	Body feels less solid
	•	Mild euphoria / calm

⸻

2. 🔥 Lock Mode (focus / hunter mode)

Goal: sharp, controlled, present

Protocol:
	•	Breath: short + strong (in 3, out 3)
	•	Eyes: fixed on one point
	•	Jaw: slightly clenched
	•	Phrase:
“Narrow. Lock. Execute.”

Expected effect:
	•	Tunnel vision
	•	Reduced distraction
	•	Increased reaction speed

⸻

3. 🪶 Calm Mode (baseline reset)

Goal: stable, grounded, no noise

Protocol:
	•	Breath: long exhale (inhale 4, exhale 8–10)
	•	Shoulders: drop
	•	Focus: chest or stomach
	•	Phrase:
“Nothing to solve. Just here.”

Expected effect:
	•	Nervous system downshift
	•	Clear thinking
	•	Emotional neutrality

⸻

🧩 The Key Upgrade (this is where it gets powerful)

Anchor Creation (VERY important)

Pick a physical trigger for each mode:
	•	Float → rub thumb + index finger together
	•	Lock → press tongue to roof of mouth
	•	Calm → slow exhale + drop shoulders

While you’re IN the state:
→ repeat the trigger

Do this 5–10 times across sessions.

Your brain links:
trigger → state

Now you can activate it fast.

⸻

⚡ Fast Activation (once trained)

After a few sessions:
	•	Float mode → 10–20 seconds
	•	Lock mode → almost instant
	•	Calm mode → 1–2 breaths

